  <channel>
    <title>CKAN: Ticket #1650: Add new language/translation of fields for datasets.</title>
    <link>http://localhost/ticket/1650</link>
    <description>&lt;p&gt;
Datasets should have a field that specifies the language used in the dataset, this should be a two character ISO 639-1 code (see &lt;a class="ext-link" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes"&gt;&lt;span class="icon"&gt;â€‹&lt;/span&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes&lt;/a&gt; for list) . Also make sure all tests and migrations are resolved. [2d]
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Determine the best approach to having 'translation_of' references to show which dataset the current one is a translation of.  This may be a translation of field, or a 'copied from' field or another form of package relationship. [2d]
&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
